  "title" : "Where is the documentation for the values() method of Enum?",
  "body" : "<p>I declare an enum as : </p>\n\n<pre><code>enum Sex {MALE,FEMALE};\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And then, iterate enum as shown below :</p>\n\n<pre><code>for(Sex v : Sex.values()){\n    System.out.println(\" values :\"+ v);\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I checked the Java API but can't find the values() method? I'm curious as to where this method comes from? </p>\n\n<p>API link : \n<a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Enum.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Enum.html</a></p>\n"
}